TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(10,40,1);

BEGIN_TEXT
Suppose the function \(f(x)\) is an odd function and 
\(\lim_{x\to\infty} f(x) = $a \). Use this information to evaluate \(\lim_{x\to -\infty} f(x) .\)
$BR$BR
Answer: \{ans_rule()\}

END_TEXT


ANS(num_cmp(-$a));
